  You should enable assert keyword in java compiler as well as in JRE.
  Java Compiler: In window-&gt;preference-&gt;Java-&gt;Compiler-&gt;Compliance and
Classfiles, set all levels to 1.4
  JRE: Just as Benedict Heal said&quot;window/preferences/java/installed
JREs, edit the JRE, and set the vmargs to -ea&quot;

  Also, if you only want to enable assert keyword in several projects,
you can set the project&#39;s preference and &quot;Run...&quot; preference.
  Java Compiler: In Project-&gt;Preference-&gt;Java-&gt;Compiler-&gt;Compliance
and Classfiles.
  JRE: Run-&gt;Run..., select your junit case and then in Arguments-&gt;VM
Arguments add -ea.



